data.name: storeTrackIdsInCustomTagCheckBoxLabel.ToolTip
data.value:
Backup/restore relies on MusicBee internal track IDs specific to the library. Because of this, you can't restore tags to a library other than the library from which the tags have been backed up. If you tick this option, the plugin will save a copy of the track IDs to a custom tag of your choice and will restore backed-up tags using this custom tag to identify tracks instead of actual track IDs.
This will let you restore the tags to the new library containing the same tracks, if you have recreated the library from scratch, e.g., on another computer.
Make sure that this custom tag is stored in the file tag, not in the MusicBee database.
